{"TopicId":196240,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"finding autopilot mode in the background","CreatedByName":"FreeThinker","CreatedById":117389,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-11T11:37:53Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"FreeThinker","CreatedById":117389,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-11T11:37:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuestion: How to get a vessel active autopilot mode while a vessel is unloaded?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was able to find throtle, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E shouldn\u0027t be that far off\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI cannot find it anywhere in the save file. It almost as if it in simply not stored\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-11T11:49:21Z\u0022 title=\u002208/11/2020 11:49  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 11, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by FreeThinker\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aniruddh","CreatedById":173854,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-11T12:47:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnless you have to have the vessel actively steer to the correct orientation based on autopilot mode when unloaded, here is an idea I though of (unless you\u0027ve already tried this):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could create a custom field in the save file under the right vessel\u0027s name, that stores the autopilot mode. You could do this using a KSPField while the vessel is loaded. When the vessel becomes unloaded, you could retrieve the value by loading the save file as a config node, and finding the right vessel using for loops and then retrieve the value.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-11T12:50:13Z\u0022 title=\u002208/11/2020 12:50  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 11, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Aniruddh\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FreeThinker","CreatedById":117389,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-11T12:54:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/173854-aniruddh/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022173854\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/173854-aniruddh/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Aniruddh\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0\u00A0 I already did something like that, but it isn\u0027t ideal as it requires you to load the vessel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-11T12:58:36Z\u0022 title=\u002208/11/2020 12:58  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 11, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by FreeThinker\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aniruddh","CreatedById":173854,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-11T14:05:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223835885\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196240\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221597150487\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022117389\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FreeThinker\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, FreeThinker said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/173854-aniruddh/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022173854\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/173854-aniruddh/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Aniruddh\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0\u00A0 I already did something like that, but it isn\u0027t ideal as it requires you to load the vessel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot really the vessel itself, but you would have to load the save file, which I guess could affect performance?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FreeThinker","CreatedById":117389,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-11T14:30:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223835917\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196240\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221597154711\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173854\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aniruddh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, Aniruddh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot really the vessel itself, but you would have to load the save file, which I guess could affect performance?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo what I mean is you have to switch to the vessel (or some vessel in physics range) before you get access to active autopilot mode. A partmodule or vesselmodule or scenariomodule can then readout the active autopilot state.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-11T14:31:27Z\u0022 title=\u002208/11/2020 02:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 11, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by FreeThinker\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"garwel","CreatedById":141813,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-22T17:36:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you mean the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E mode, it\u0027s in Vessel.Autopilot.Mode.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPS: Oh, I didn\u0027t realize you want to find it in the save. Are you sure it\u0027s even saved? I think it only applies to the active vessel. Perhaps, you can save it manually to a custom VesselModule (and then restore when the vessel is loaded).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-22T17:39:11Z\u0022 title=\u002208/22/2020 05:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 22, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by garwel\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansAcker","CreatedById":195534,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-24T15:11:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223842313\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196240\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221598117776\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022141813\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022garwel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/22/2020 at 7:36 PM, garwel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, I didn\u0027t realize you want to find it in the save. Are you sure it\u0027s even saved?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E _mode_ (prograde/radial/etc.) is not saved unless helped by a mod.. The on/off state is saved in the ActionGroups section and can be accessed in-game via Vessel.ActionGroups[KSPActionGroup.\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E];\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}